Let's face it, Adamski was never going to better the titular masterful synth classic, which also catapulted the strapping soulful powerhouse Seal to international stardom. However, tracks such as N-R-G, his first hit, the catchy I Dream of You, and quirky late chart-troubling singles such as the Elvis-sampling Space Jungle and rave-oriented Flashback Jack, from the underwhelming Doctor Adamski's Musical Pharmacy long-player, stand the test of time surprisingly well, and remind us that Adamski should be remembered as more than just a footnote on the early 90s Electronic revival.
Amazon Review by By Scaroth, Last of the Jagaroth.
